  "market_context": "RBOB Gasoline opens the day low, respecting the upper half (equilibrium) of the previous day's range, setting up a potential bullish daily candle with a draw on liquidity to higher time frame buy-side liquidity above.",
  "key_observation": "Two-stage SMT on the 4-hour between candle 1 and candle 2 confirms the low of day inside a daily fair value gap, followed by a V-shaped reversal — the textbook reversal signature — with expansion toward HTF draw on liquidity.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily, mark the daily open and note that price opens low while respecting the equilibrium of the previous day's range — ideal bullish daily candle formation.",
    "Step 2: Drop to the 4-hour and identify a two-stage SMT between candle 1 and candle 2 inside the previous day's daily fair value gap, confirming the low of the day.",
    "Step 3: Recognize the phase of price after the SMT — a V-shaped reversal — as the reversal signature, with HTF draw on liquidity above as the overall target.",
    "Step 4: Observe expansion away from the low leaving multiple failure swings (LRL), confirming a continuation signature into the upper half of the previous day's range fair value gap.",
    "Step 5: Drop to the 30-minute to visualize price trading into the key level and expanding away, forming the V-shape that confirms the low of the day.",
    "Step 6: Move to the 1-hour to identify a continuation PSP — not a reversal PSP — since draw liquidity remains open above; opposing PSPs in continuation are not reversal signals.",
    "Step 7: Drop to the 1-minute (lower time frame) and enter on a fair value gap during the continuation around 8:00, targeting the HTF high for ~2.8R."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade taken on continuation FVG entry around 8:00, targeted HTF high for ~2.8R — price expanded cleanly all the way to draw on liquidity.",
  "lessons": "When draw on liquidity remains open, opposing PSPs should be read as continuation signals, not reversal triggers. Ideal entries are at the actual two-stage SMT, but continuation entries on the LTF FVG still deliver high R when aligned top-down.",
